** Bellwether ** are Principal Contractors delivering construction projects who also provide engineering support services to private and government clients across Australia.   
  
Projects we’ve successfully delivered throughout Queensland include flood
recovery works, streetscapes, road construction / upgrades, bulk earthworks,
bridges, and water infrastructure.  
  
We pride ourselves on living and breathing our Core Values, and we go the
extra mile for each other and our clients.  
We’re a supportive team with a direct line of contact to the Directors, a new
fleet of vehicles, and we can offer all-inclusive renumeration packages.  
  
We’re looking for Graduate Civil Engineers (recent Graduates, or up to 2
years' experience), to join our team. This role will be based in Brisbane,
however there will be a requirement from time to time to work away to support
various projects on a DIDO arrangement.  
  
You’ll need to demonstrate the following:  

  * Completion of a relevant tertiary qualification that is ideally supported by some industry experience 
  * Exposure to Quality Assurance 
  * Experience in using or have had exposure to Civil Pro, CAD, AutoCAD, MicroStation or other drafting software 
  * Strong Microsoft Office Word and Excel skills 
  * Strong communication skills, written and oral 
  * Manual Driver’s License 
  * Construction White card 
  * Must be willing to DIDO / FIFO if required (Monday - Friday only) 
Your technical skills will be supported by an enthusiastic, proactive and
positive attitude and a strong desire to learn from senior managers.  
  
Our organisation is growing, this is an exciting opportunity for someone to
further develop and diversify their skills and be given the opportunity to
work on some of Australia’s biggest and most challenging projects.  
  
** Bellwether ** provide opportunities for career development and the chance to be influential in the overall growth of the business. We’re committed to continuous improvement and have a strong focus on safety. This is a great opportunity to broaden your skills whilst developing in our friendly, professional, and collaborative environment.   
  
** Your Resume should include: ** your personal mobile phone, email, residential home base suburb and current assignment/employment end date or notice period.   
  
** For best results, apply directly via our website:   
** www.bellwether.com.au   
  
You must have the right to work in Australia & have local work experience. We
collect & store your personal details strictly according to Australian Privacy
Laws, confidentiality is assured and we always contact you first before
sharing your profile with our clients. Applications accepted from Candidates
only. (No agencies please).

